cs.RO, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.HC, cs.SY

Reasoning: 
- cs.RO (Robotics) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on teaching robots to perform tasks through human corrections. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also likely as the paper discusses the use of machine learning techniques for the robot to learn from human corrections. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is relevant as the paper introduces a Kalman filter for learning from corrections. 
- cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) is relevant as the paper discusses the interaction between humans and robots in the context of teaching and learning. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is also relevant as the paper discusses the deployment of the robot in a risk-sensitive manner.
